Description: Fragment of handle with gradual curve of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp with pilos and star symbols. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Name Iason. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 80, 7. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0640.08.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1048)
